{
  "text": "Serapie mice. Animals were injected i.c. or i.p. with a 1% (w/v) homogenate (0.02 ml) of brain from a terminal case of mouse scrapie. Two inbred strains of mice, VM/Dk (Sinc pT) and VM (Sind v) congenics (Bruce et al., 1991; [CITATION_1] and their FI cross (Sinc~TPT), were inoculated with two scrapie strains, ME7 and 22A . The ME7 strain of scrapie had been serially passaged through Sine ~7 mice and the 22A strain through S#tc p7 mice. VM/Dk mice were infected i.c. with a 1% (w/v) homogenate, and IM/Dk mice (also Sine ~v) were infected with a 10 % homogenate of87V scrapie brain [CITATION_2] . The incubation period data are given in Table 1. Animals were sacrificed by cervical dislocation and their tissues frozen in liquid nitrogen before storage at -70 \u00b0C. Brain, spleen, pancreas, submaxillary glands, thymus, and pooled subcutaneous and cervical lymph nodes were collected from each animal. Organs were also collected from uninjected and normal brain homogenate-injected, age-matched, control animals.",
